{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/mastering-paper/switching-tools/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Paper for iOS quick tip: switching tools","date":"2016-05-16T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"May 16th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","last_modified_at":"2019-09-13T19:02:11.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"10 months ago","path":"/mastering-paper/switching-tools/","author":null,"excerpt":"Switching tools in Paper for iOS may seem obvious to you pros out there, but you'd be surprised how often I'm asked how to do it. Here's the answer.","tags":["Paper for iOS","Apple","tutorial"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":4.296875,"src":"/static/7092c99bb19914157a90e4ac360f4082/fc20c/paper-53-full-tools.jpg","srcSet":"/static/7092c99bb19914157a90e4ac360f4082/6e883/paper-53-full-tools.jpg 275w,\n/static/7092c99bb19914157a90e4ac360f4082/a09ef/paper-53-full-tools.jpg 550w,\n/static/7092c99bb19914157a90e4ac360f4082/fc20c/paper-53-full-tools.jpg 1100w,\n/static/7092c99bb19914157a90e4ac360f4082/297b5/paper-53-full-tools.jpg 1587w","sizes":"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px"},"fixed":{"src":"/static/7092c99bb19914157a90e4ac360f4082/fc20c/paper-53-full-tools.jpg","height":256,"width":1100}}},"toc":true,"comments":true,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":null},"id":"6e72debe-adf4-5fb6-8d52-c4ad822e04e0","html":"<p>New to Paper by FiftyThree and can’t seem to figure out how to switch tools? I have the short answer for you right here.</p>\n<p>They may be subtle, but the white dots beneath the row of tools are a big clue to help solve this mystery. Similar to the dots you find at the bottom of your iOS device’s home screen, they indicate there are off-screen goodies to be had.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 900px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 27.636363636363637%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"indicator dots beneath Paper tools\"\n        title=\"indicator dots beneath Paper tools\"\n        data-src=\"/static/c440ab1af0b610d1797c0ab6b7a3b987/062c0/paper-53-switch-tools-dots.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/c440ab1af0b610d1797c0ab6b7a3b987/16841/paper-53-switch-tools-dots.jpg 275w,\n/static/c440ab1af0b610d1797c0ab6b7a3b987/50c97/paper-53-switch-tools-dots.jpg 550w,\n/static/c440ab1af0b610d1797c0ab6b7a3b987/062c0/paper-53-switch-tools-dots.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"tool-switching-ipad\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tool-switching-ipad\" aria-label=\"tool switching ipad permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tool switching (iPad)</h2>\n<p>Swipe across the row of <strong>Think Kit</strong> tools to reveal another set of five (<a href=\"/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/#fountain-pen\">Fountain Pen</a>, <a href=\"/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/#pencil\">Pencil</a>, <a href=\"/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/#marker\">Marker</a>, <a href=\"/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/#ink-pen\">Fine Tip Ink Pen</a>, and <a href=\"/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/#watercolor-brush\">Watercolor Brush</a>) to the right.</p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.42857142857143%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; \" > <div class=\"embedVideo-container\"> <iframe data-src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/KXqj04MfDLk?rel=0\" class=\"embedVideo-iframe lazyload\" style=\"border:0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \" allowfullscreen></iframe> </div> </div></p>\n<h2 id=\"tool-switching-iphone\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tool-switching-iphone\" aria-label=\"tool switching iphone permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tool switching (iPhone)</h2>\n<p>And for you iPhone Paper users there are three sets of tools you can swipe through.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/5c3426344ddec75c2398cdbdbaa4c36d/paper-53-switch-tools-iphone.gif\" alt=\"switching tools in Paper by 53 for the iPhone\"></p>\n<p>I know what you’re thinking, “wow how could anyone miss this?” Well from the amount of emails I receive a month asking how to change tools… quite a lot.</p>","excerpt":"New to Paper by FiftyThree and can’t seem to figure out how to switch tools? I have the short answer for you right here. They may be subtle…","timeToRead":1,"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/switching-tools/#tool-switching-ipad\">Tool switching (iPad)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/mastering-paper/switching-tools/#tool-switching-iphone\">Tool switching (iPhone)</a></li>\n</ul>"},"comments":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"b17a92de-7ed6-5304-adaa-b305a6022863","frontmatter":{"name":"Mikef2007","email":null,"friendlyDate":"July 03, 2016","iso8601Date":"2016-07-03T19:03:06.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>How do I type on a picture I’ve imported?</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"312af7dc-243b-5cef-83c4-d4ccd5fc6209","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"July 03, 2016","iso8601Date":"2016-07-03T23:39:41.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>You can’t add text directly on top of images you import. You can only add text\nas note below them.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"1b2f931d-93db-564e-a067-0c5e2642e885","frontmatter":{"name":"Carroll Durodola","email":"e3bd2a466add75b3bc893a9b41f1e14b","friendlyDate":"December 15, 2016","iso8601Date":"2016-12-15T15:08:24.335Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Can I save my work as 300dpi so it is printable in Paper53? My iPad is old, I\ncan’t get Photoshop, Procreate keeps popping off my screen. I’m trying to find\nan app that will let me save as 300 dpi. HELP!</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"19dc5aed-2b9a-5579-a89c-c072c858a111","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"December 17, 2016","iso8601Date":"2016-12-17T02:17:00.089Z","published":null},"html":"<p>When you export Paper ideas to your camera roll they’re saved at the same\nresolution as your iPad’s screen — which varies on what model you have (Pro\n12″, Air, Mini, etc.)</p>\n<p>They also come out at 72 dpi I believe, so you’d need an app that can resample\nit to 300. On my Air 2 images are <code class=\"language-text\">2048 x 1536</code> which @ 300 dpi comes out to be\n6.827 x 5.12 inches… more than enough to print a 4 x 6.</p>\n<p>You can certainly go larger, but there will likely be some image quality loss. I\nhad one of\n<a href=\"https://mademistakes.com/paperfaces/luke-skywalker-cave-portrait/\">my drawings blown up</a>\nand printed at 40″ wide and it looks fine. It really depends on the image\nthough.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"650e79d5-6ccf-5500-87a0-8fa6cbca76a3","frontmatter":{"name":"Cheryl","email":"2aaee6e84eeae17b949fc33976219d3c","friendlyDate":"October 03, 2017","iso8601Date":"2017-10-03T02:29:30.257Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Is there a way to widen the width of the pencil or brush or? And do you have a\nstylus you recommend?</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"41c36506-756d-5ada-84cb-ce2035e3b605","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"October 03, 2017","iso8601Date":"2017-10-03T11:04:19.958Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Yes you can change the width of the tools by either using styli that are\npressure sensitive like Apple Pencil, or\n<a href=\"https://mademistakes.com/mastering-paper/introduction-tool-guide/\">varying the speed</a>\nat width you draw/paint.</p>\n<p>Here are all the\n<a href=\"https://mademistakes.com/faqs/stylus-recommendations/\">styli I’ve used</a> and my\nthoughts on them. If you have an iPad Pro I’d recommend Apple Pencil.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"15cf411e-138e-5763-b831-cc4d09694b37","frontmatter":{"name":"Robin Baron","email":"adf797a8ef1093fa0ee9ca2f380d3052","friendlyDate":"December 19, 2017","iso8601Date":"2017-12-19T00:55:33.495Z","published":null},"html":"<p>How do I import a picture from photo library and edit and email it..?</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"5dd1e84f-b9b4-5a64-b973-9558ea3b54ec","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"December 20, 2017","iso8601Date":"2017-12-20T19:58:10.768Z","published":null},"html":"<p>There is a new tool to the far right of the color wheel (you may need to swipe\nthe tools to reveal it) called <strong>Canvas</strong>. Tap that and you can import a photo\nonto the canvas or use one of the included templates.</p>\n<p>For additional reference see\n<a href=\"https://wetransfer.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360001333846-Canvas-Drawing-Tools\">Paper’s support site</a>.</p>"}}]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/procreate-paintings/maria-g-portrait/","title":"Nose ring oil","categories":["procreate-paintings"],"tags":["Procreate","portrait","illustration","Sktchy","time lapse"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/procreate-paintings/maria-g-portrait.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/procreate-paintings/emil-i-portrait/","title":"Watercolor, not watercolor","categories":["procreate-paintings"],"tags":["Procreate","portrait","illustration","Sktchy","time lapse"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/procreate-paintings/emil-i-portrait.md"}}}}